Former BBNaija housemate, ‘Uriel’ Ngozi Oputa has shared how her ex-boyfriend made her feel terribly insecure about her body. The reality TV star said the ex constantly taunted her with a scar on her leg. According to Uriel, her ex always said her legs were not fine because of the scar which largely affected her self-confidence.   Mary Njoku: quit age-shaming or else…     Many unsuccessful years behind every successful man, not…     I still breastfeed my daughter at almost three – TBoss   “I remember my ex said my legs weren’t fine because I had a scar. He made feel so bad. I lost confidence,” she wrote. She however noted the situation is different now as those legs for which she was constantly taunted are being called “beautiful”. The entrepreneur added: “This life ehn! When he is not for you, he is truly not for you. There will always be someone who is ready to massage those scars.”